f=Engineering/quinn/custom/charter-enforcement/assets/plan-lock-log-template.md · h1:Plan-Lock Log [business name]=Rail 1's append-only ledger. One entry lock event; entries NEVER edited deleted corrections outcomes new entries referencing original. Tamper-evident hash chain: entry records previous entry's hash. **Log path (config):** `plan_lock_log` **Hash algorithm:** [default SHA-256] **Maintained by:** quinn · h1:Plan-Lock Log [business name]=\| # \| Plan ID \| Agent \| Plan hash \| Prev-entry hash \| Locked at \| Supersedes \| Outcome (later entry ref) \| · h1:Plan-Lock Log [business name]=\|---\|---------\|-------\|-----------\|-----------------\|-----------\|------------\|---------------------------\| · h1:Plan-Lock Log [business name]=\| 1 \| <FILL_IN> \| <FILL_IN> \| <FILL_IN> \| — (genesis) \| <FILL_IN> \| — \| — \| · h2:Entry types=**LOCK** plan validated frozen; agent begin., **HALT** off-plan call detected: records executed call, locked plan's delta, escalation ref., **RELOCK** new plan superseding prior one (cites it); old plan's work stops under old lock., **OUTCOME** run completed on-plan halted step abandoned; closes LOCK entry reference., **DENIAL** Rail egress denial Rail destructive-op detection, logged one audit trail. · ru:s=Append-only; corrections new entry referencing old (`corrects: #N`), never edit., entry carries previous entry's hash broken chain itself top-severity finding., quinn's plans locked like any agent's, hashed before quinn's run begins.